11/04/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Thousands of high school students protested in several provinces across the country on Saturday (April 9th) and Sunday against the country's testing authority amid allegations of possible cheating surfaced involving a recent university entrance exam.
The YGS national exam was taken by about 1.7 million students in March.
A recent allegation suggested answers to the test could be found using a special code, spurring a heated debate across the country.
According to local media, the weekend protests were organised via Facebook.
(Hurriyet - 10/04/11;
Dogan - 09/04/11)
